{{one source|date=February 2015}} {{Spelling bee | name = 25th National Geographic Bee <!-- Commented out: | image = NationalGeographicBeeOfficialLogo.png --> | caption = | date = May 22, 2013 | location = [[Washington, D.C.]] | winner = Sathwik Karnik | age = 12 | residence = [[Plainville, Massachusetts]] | word = | contestants = 54 | moderator = | Preceded by = [[24th National Geographic Bee]] | Followed by = [[26th National Geographic Bee]] }} The '''25th [[National Geographic Bee]]''' was held in [[Washington, D.C.]] on May 22, 2013, sponsored by the [[National Geographic Society]].
Twelve-year-old Sathwik Karnik, from [[Plainville, Massachusetts]] won the competition, beating out 52 other competitors representing the 50 U.S. states, Pacific territories, and [[United States Department of Defense|Department of Defense]] dependent schools.<ref>[http://newsfeed.time.com/2013/05/23/massachusetts-boy-wins-geography-bee/]</ref>
