{{Infobox university | image = [[Image:hulogo.jpg|Haramaya University]] | name = Haramaya University | native_name = | established = 1953 | type = [[National university|National]] | city = [[Haramaya]] | country = [[Ethiopia]] | language = English | president = Chemeda Finensa | enrollment = 33,555 (2015/16) | website = {{URL|www.haramaya.edu.et/}} }} '''Haramaya University''' is a public research university in [[Haramaya]], [[Oromia Region|Oromia]], [[Ethiopia]]. It is approximately {{Convert|478|km|mi}} east of [[Addis Ababa]], Ethiopia. The [[Ministry of Education (Ethiopia)|Ministry of Education]] admits qualified students to Haramaya University based on their score on the Ethiopian Higher Education Entrance Examination (EHEEE).
== History == The Alemaya College of Agriculture was established in 1953.<ref name=":1">{{Cite book|title=The Development of Higher Education and Social Change, an Ethiopian Experience|last=Wagaw|first=Teshome|publisher=Michigan State University Press|year=1990|isbn=|location=East Lansing|pages=}}</ref> In 1994 the Alemaya University of Agriculture was established by government proclamation ([[Council of Ministers (Ethiopia)|Council of Ministers]] 198/1994).<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=23 May 2011|title=Haramaya University Establishment|url=https://chilot.me/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/reg-no-232-haremaya-university-re-establishment.pdf|journal=Federal Negarit Gazeta|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref> On 23 May 2011, the Haramaya University was established.<ref name=":0" />
==Academics== Haramaya University offers 106 undergraduate programs, 104 graduate programs, and 14 PhD programs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.haramaya.edu.et/about/|title=Historical Background of the University|last=|first=|date=|website=Haramaya University|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=7 October 2018}}</ref>
{{Div col}} *College of Agricultural and Environmental Sciences *College of Business and Economics *College of Computing and Informatics *College of Health and Medical Sciences *College of Social Science and Humanities *College of Law,College of Veterinary Medicine *College of Natural and Computational Science *Haramaya Institute of Technology *College of Education and Behavioral Sciences *School of Graduate Studies *Continuing and Distance Education Directorate {{colend}} ==Research== The University is pioneer for Agricultural research in Ethiopia. {{colend}}
== Notable alumni == *[[Gebisa Ejeta]] *Tekalign Mamo Assefa *[[Siraj Fegessa]]
