'''MonoMouse''' is a handheld electronic magnifier manufactured by Bierley.com Limited, designed to help people with a visual impairment to read printed text or images.<ref>[http://www.califa.org/monomouse.php#tab1 California Libraries], California Libraries</ref> 
<ref name="BBC Website">[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/technology/4412283.stm#tab1 BBC], BBC review</ref>

Originally developed by Ian Bierley in 2003 for use by his mother who suffered from [[Glaucoma]], and then later released as a commercial product supplied through opticians.<ref>[http://www.opticianonline.net/Articles/2005/07/22/13746/Bierley's+MonoMouse+.html#tab2 Optician Article]</ref> The MonoMouse is shaped like an oversized [[Mouse (computing)|computer mouse]] and connects to any television through either the [[SCART]] connector in Europe or the [[RCA connector]] in the rest of the world.

It is an example of [[Assistive technology]] to enable people with eye conditions like [[Macular degeneration]] to read printed text and see printed images.

