{{Infobox recurring event | name = | native_name = | logo = [[File:UCT mathematics competition logo.gif]] | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | status = Active | genre =[[Mathematics competition]] | date = | begins = | ends = | frequency = Annually | venue = [[University of Cape Town]] | location = | coordinates = {{coord|33|57|27|S|18|27|38|E|display=inline,title|region:ZA_type:edu}} | country = {{Flagicon|South Africa}} [[South Africa]] | years_active = 1977-present | first = {{Start date|1977|||df=y}} | founder_name = | last = {{date|2014|04|10|df=y}} | prev = | next = | participants = 7000 | attendance = | area = | budget = | patron = | organised = <!--"organized=" also works--> | filing = <!-- Filing status --> | people = | member = | website = {{URL|http://www.math.uct.ac.za/mam/outreach/competition}} | footnotes = }} The '''UCT Mathematics Competition''' is an annual [[list of mathematics competitions|mathematics competition]] for schools in the [[Western Cape]] province of [[South Africa]], held at the [[University of Cape Town]].
Around 7000 participants from Grade 8 to Grade 12 take part, writing a multiple-choice paper. Individual and pair entries are accepted, but all write the same paper for their grade. The current holder of the School Trophy is [[Rondebosch Boys High School]], with [[Diocesan College]] achieving second place in the 2017 competition.<ref name=Winners>{{cite web|title=Award Winners|url=http://www.math.uct.ac.za/mam/outreach/competition/winners|publisher=UCT Mathematics Competition|accessdate=28 June 2017}}</ref> These two schools have held the top positions in the competition for a number of years.
The competition was established in 1977 by Mona Leeuwenberg and Shirley Fitton, who were teachers at [[Diocesan College]] and [[Westerford High School]], and since 1987 has been run by Professor John Webb of the University of Cape Town.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.math.uct.ac.za/mam/staff/webb|title=John Webb|publisher=UCT Department of Mathematics and Applied Mathematics|accessdate=27 June 2017}}</ref>
